0:13:22.26,000 --> 0:13:25,000
If you master these, you master price,

325
0:13:25.26,000 --> 0:13:27,000
and if you don't master these, you can master

326
0:13:27.26,000 --> 0:13:29,000
the little noise as well as you can,

327
0:13:29.26,000 --> 0:13:31,000
but it's not important.

328
0:13:31.26,000 --> 0:13:33,000
Well, here are the curves for it.

329
0:13:33.26,000 --> 0:13:35,000
Now, I get to the final thing, which is the set

330
0:13:35.26,000 --> 0:13:37,000
of which my name is attached.

331
0:13:37.26,000 --> 0:13:39,000
In a way, it's the story of my life.

332
0:13:39.26,000 --> 0:13:41,000
My adolescence was spent

333
0:13:41.26,000 --> 0:13:43,000
during the German occupation of France.

334
0:13:43.26,000 --> 0:13:46,000
Since I thought that I might

335
0:13:46.26,000 --> 0:13:49,000
vanish within a day or a week,

336
0:13:49.26,000 --> 0:13:52,000
I had very big dreams.

337
0:13:52.26,000 --> 0:13:54,000
And after the war,

338
0:13:54.26,000 --> 0:13:56,000
I saw an uncle again.

339
0:13:56.26,000 --> 0:13:58,000
My uncle was a very prominent mathematician, and he told me,

340
0:13:58.26,000 --> 0:14:,000
"Look, there's a problem

341
0:14:00.26,000 --> 0:14:02,000
which I could not solve 25 years ago,

342
0:14:02.26,000 --> 0:14:04,000
and which nobody can solve.

343
0:14:04.26,000 --> 0:14:06,000
This is a construction of a man named [Gaston] Julia

344
0:14:06.26,000 --> 0:14:08,000
and [Pierre] Fatou.

345
0:14:08.26,000 --> 0:14:1,000
If you could

346
0:14:10.26,000 --> 0:14:12,000
find something new, anything,

347
0:14:12.26,000 --> 0:14:14,000
you will get your career made."

348
0:14:14.26,000 --> 0:14:16,000
Very simple.

349
0:14:16.26,000 --> 0:14:18,000
So I looked,

350
0:14:18.26,000 --> 0:14:2,000
and like the thousands of people that had tried before,

351
0:14:20.26,000 --> 0:14:23,000
I found nothing.

352
0:14:23.26,000 --> 0:14:25,000
But then the computer came,

353
0:14:25.26,000 --> 0:14:27,000
and I decided to apply the computer,

354
0:14:27.26,000 --> 0:14:3,000
not to new problems in mathematics --

355
0:14:30.26,000 --> 0:14:32,000
like this wiggle wiggle, that's a new problem --

356
0:14:32.26,000 --> 0:14:34,000
but to old problems.

357
0:14:34.26,000 --> 0:14:36,000
And I went from what's called

358
0:14:36.26,000 --> 0:14:38,000
real numbers, which are points on a line,

359
0:14:38.26,000 --> 0:14:4,000
to imaginary, complex numbers,

360
0:14:40.26,000 --> 0:14:42,000
which are points on a plane,

361
0:14:42.26,000 --> 0:14:44,000
which is what one should do there,

362
0:14:44.26,000 --> 0:14:46,000
and this shape came out.

363
0:14:46.26,000 --> 0:14:49,000
This shape is of an extraordinary complication.

364
0:14:49.26,000 --> 0:14:51,000
The equation is hidden there,

365
0:14:51.26,000 --> 0:14:54,000
z goes into z squared, plus c.

366
0:14:54.26,000 --> 0:14:56,000
It's so simple, so dry.

367
0:14:56.26,000 --> 0:14:58,000
It's so uninteresting.

368
0:14:58.26,000 --> 0:15:01,000
Now you turn the crank once, twice:

369
0:15:01.26,000 --> 0:15:04,000
twice,

370
0:15:04.26,000 --> 0:15:06,000
marvels come out.

371
0:15:06.26,000 --> 0:15:08,000
I mean this comes out.

372
0:15:08.26,000 --> 0:15:1,000
I don't want to explain these things.

373
0:15:10.26,000 --> 0:15:12,000
This comes out. This comes out.

374
0:15:12.26,000 --> 0:15:14,000
Shapes which are of such complication,

375
0:15:14.26,000 --> 0:15:17,000
such harmony and such beauty.

376
0:15:17.26,000 --> 0:15:19,000
This comes out

377
0:15:19.26,000 --> 0:15:21,000
repeatedly, again, again, again.

378
0:15:21.26,000 --> 0:15:23,000
And that was one of my major discoveries,

379
0:15:23.26,000 --> 0:15:25,000
to find that these islands were the same

380
0:15:25.26,000 --> 0:15:27,000
as the whole big thing, more or less.

381
0:15:27.26,000 --> 0:15:29,000
And then you get these

382
0:15:29.26,000 --> 0:15:32,000
extraordinary baroque decorations all over the place.

383
0:15:32.26,000 --> 0:15:35,000
All that from this little formula,

384
0:15:35.26,000 --> 0:15:38,000
which has whatever, five symbols in it.

385
0:15:38.26,000 --> 0:15:4,000
And then this one.

386
0:15:40.26,000 --> 0:15:42,000
The color was added for two reasons.

